    {
        "name": "_FancyText Unicode_",
        "category": "⚑ FancyText Unicode ⚑",
        "civilopediaText": [
            {  "text": "UTF-8 Symbols", "header": 1, },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "A dual-purpose mod:", },
            {  "text": "    1. Pre-pend unicode symbols to city names", },
            {  "text": "    2. Unicode character rendering checker", },
            {  "text": "", },

            {  "text": "Make city names more referential", "header": 1, },
            {  "text": "Using symbols in unit or city names adds a fun and readable attribute! ♬", "starred":true, },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "All capitol cities ⭐ and city-states ⟰ in this mod have a symbol prefix.", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "
Aliased cities look like:

Babylon = ⭐Babylon
Athens = ⭐Athens
Beijing = ⭐Beijing
...
Brussels = ⟰Brussels
Bucharest = ⟰Bucharest
Florence = ⟰Florence
...", },
            {  "text": "See: jsons/English.properties",
               "link": "https://github.com/hackedpassword/FancyText-Unicode/blob/main/jsons/translations/English.properties",
               "color": "#00FFFF",
               "size": 16, },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "separator": true, },

            {  "header": 1, "text": "Uses: City/Unit names", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "⚔ Improve *sorting* city/unit names and labels in various screens and menus!", },
            {  "text": "⚔ Better unit identification at-a-glance!", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "header": 1, "text": "Uses: Examples", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "By adding a symbol prefix to a name:", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "❈ The spy_screen cities will auto-sort based on Capitols and CS's", },
            {  "text": "❈ The city_screen [city name] reveals if this city is a CS or Capitol", },
            {  "text": "❈ The unit_screen can auto-sort by special cities", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "By adding prefix symbol badges to high ranking units, this helps manage unit strategy faster.", },
            {  "text": "Different unit types or groups can be assigned their own ranks (manually of course, just another way to crawl).", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "header": 1, "text": "Uses: Advanced assets", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "An even more clever use is for naming mod assets in very unique ways.", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "Rather than a long description, a unicode symbol says it all, i.e.:
  ⮝ ╦.png", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "..says this asset has reduced a descriptive name from 5 words to 2 symbols, describing an upper aligned top-to-bottom T-intersection.", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "Add unit prefixes like in these examples:

☮ Great Prophet
⚛ GDR Boss
⚍ Lt Cmdr
⛉⛉⛉ Sky Admiral (3rd rank)
⚑⭐ Washington (the additional flag tells me this is _my_ capital city, vs _other_ captured capitals)", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "separator": true, },
            {  "text": "☣ Gotchas ☣", "header": 5, },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "  ☹ Copying characters? There does not appear to be a way to highlight-select text in-game, other than from city or unit renaming.", },
            {  "text": "  ☹ «#ff0000»You cannot copy characters from this help screen!«» See below.", },
            {  "text": "  ☹ 😝 ☹ 😛 ← the Emoji Faces (Smileys) pictograph set doesn't work. Other basic emojis do ☠ ☺", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "separator": true, },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "To use these symbols for your cities or units:", "starred": true, },
            {  "text": "
▸ «#00FFFF»tap the link«» under the sections' preview block which opens Firefox etc,
▸ «#00FFFF»copy the symbol«» from your browser,
▸ «#00FFFF»paste into an Unciv textbox«» from in-game.", },
            {  "text": "", },
            {  "text": "The FancyText sections here are known good rendering Unicode blocks. Pictograph symbols generally don't work. More sections to be added.", },

        ]
    },
